- e2e/side-panel-npm-search.e2e.ts (add test to the same file as US-002)

Context:
This test needs `NPM_CONFIG_PREFIX` to isolate the npm install. The server must also have `OPENTABS_SKIP_NPM_DISCOVERY: undefined` so the newly installed plugin is discovered.

The install flow in the side panel:
1. User clicks Install button on NpmPluginCard
2. `onInstall(result.name)` fires → App.tsx `handleInstallPlugin` → `installPlugin(name)` from bridge.ts
3. `installingPlugins` Set gets the package name → NpmPluginCard shows `<Loader>` instead of 'Install'
4. Bridge sends `bg:installPlugin` → background → WebSocket → server `plugin.install` → `npm install -g` → rediscovery
5. Server sends `plugins.changed` notification → side panel calls `getFullState()` → plugin now in `plugins` array
6. SearchResults filters out installed plugins from npm results (line 84-85): `const installedShortNames = new Set(plugins.map(p => extractShortName(p.name)));`
7. The plugin now appears under 'Installed' section and is gone from 'Available'

The NpmPluginCard Install button:
```tsx
<Button size="sm" variant="default" disabled={installing} onClick={onInstall} className="shrink-0">
  {installing ? <Loader size="sm" /> : 'Install'}
</Button>
```

