Add a test that installs a plugin first (as setup), then uninstalls it through the UI:

```typescript
test('uninstall plugin via three-dot menu and confirmation dialog', async () => {
  test.slow();
  // Setup: same as US-003 — install a plugin first
  // ...

  // After install, clear the search to return to the main plugin list
  await sidePanelPage.getByPlaceholder('Search plugins and tools...').fill('');

  // Wait for the plugin card to appear in the main list
  const pluginTrigger = sidePanelPage.locator('button[aria-expanded]').filter({ hasText: 'Slack' });
  await expect(pluginTrigger).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });

  // Expand the card to reveal the three-dot menu
  await pluginTrigger.click();
  await expect(pluginTrigger).toHaveAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');

  // Find the three-dot menu button scoped to this card
  // PluginCard structure: Accordion.Item > [header with trigger + menu] > [content]
  // The menu button is a sibling of the trigger inside the header
  const pluginCard = pluginTrigger.locator('xpath=ancestor::div[@data-radix-accordion-item]');
  const menuButton = pluginCard.getByLabel('Plugin options');
  await menuButton.click();

  // Click 'Uninstall' in the dropdown menu
  await sidePanelPage.getByRole('menuitem', { name: 'Uninstall' }).click();

  // Confirmation dialog appears — click the destructive 'Uninstall' button
  const dialog = sidePanelPage.locator('[role=dialog]');
  await expect(dialog).toBeVisible();
  await dialog.getByRole('button', { name: 'Uninstall' }).click();

  // Wait for the plugin card to disappear
  await expect(pluginTrigger).toBeHidden({ timeout: 30_000 });

  // Verify via MCP that the plugin tools are gone
  const tools = await mcpClient.listTools();
  expect(tools.some(t => t.name.startsWith('slack_'))).toBe(false);
});
```

Locator considerations:
- The Radix Accordion Item has `data-radix-accordion-item` attribute — use it to scope the menu button.
- The menu dropdown uses `role="menuitem"` for items.
- The confirmation dialog uses `role="dialog"`.
- After clicking 'Uninstall' in the dialog, the removal starts: `npm uninstall -g` runs, then rediscovery. Wait for the card to disappear with a generous timeout.

Alternative approach: combine US-003 and US-004 into a single test that installs and then uninstalls. This avoids the need to install twice and keeps the test more efficient. The stories are separate for clarity but the implementation can be a single test function that covers both flows.

Constraints:
- Use the same `NPM_CONFIG_PREFIX` temp dir as the install test.
- The uninstall timeout should be generous (30s) since npm uninstall -g + rediscovery takes time.
- Clean up the temp prefix dir in the finally block.
- The three-dot menu button may be visually overlapping with the accordion trigger — use `{ force: true }` on the click if needed.
- The 'Uninstall' button appears BOTH in the menu and the confirmation dialog. Scope carefully: use `getByRole('menuitem')` for the menu, `dialog.getByRole('button')` for the dialog.
